Title: Aspects of BRST Quantization

Authors: J.W. van Holten

Comments: Lectures presented at the summerschool `Geometry and Topology in

Physics', Rot a/d/ Rot (Germany), sept. 2001; 75 pagesBRST-methods provide elegant and powerful tools for the construction andanalysis of constrained systems, including models of particles, strings andfields. These lectures provide an elementary introduction to the ideas,illustrated with some important physical applications.